  "body": "System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: geth version\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.9.25-stable\r\nGit Commit: e787272\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [65 64 63]\r\nGo Version: go1.15.6\r\nOperating System: linux\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=go\r\n\r\nExpected behaviour: Full node synch\r\nActual behaviour: Multiple WARN errors\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce:\r\ngeth.service file:\r\n\r\n[Unit]\r\nDescription=Go Ethereum client\r\nAfter=network.target\r\nWants=network.target\r\n\r\n[Service]\r\nUser=goeth\r\nGroup=goeth\r\nType=simple\r\nRestart=always\r\nRestartSec=5\r\nExecStart=geth --http --datadir /var/lib/goethereum --cache 4096 --maxpeers 30\r\n\r\n[Install]\r\nWantedBy=default.target\r\n\r\nHi, my node stopped being active since today. I did an update but it is still not syncing. See screenshot below. Can anyone help how to fix this, I had no issues before. \r\n![grafik](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40612817/107144714-48c93700-693d-11eb-92bf-7068b0635d4d.png)\r\n\r\nIt also says \"invaid block body RLP\" and \"sync panic:runtime error: invalid memeory address or nil pointer dereference\"\r\n\r\n![grafik](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40612817/107148542-065f2480-6954-11eb-94fa-bc818ed1410e.png)\r\n\r\nSee here: SIGSEGV: segmentation violation code=0x1 addr=0x0 pc=0x78ec7a\r\n\r\n![grafik](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40612817/107247327-72fc2100-6a31-11eb-8760-b18f2d86077b.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nMeanthwile I deleted the geth db file and did a resync. But I get the same error \"exit-code\" as above.\r\n\r\nResync failed. The log looks strange.\r\n\r\n![grafik](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40612817/107159850-e7cc4e00-6992-11eb-8d6f-393582a1dbef.png)\r\n\r\nYour feedback is much appreciated.\r\nThanks!\r\n",
